Count 2 - Felony Bail Jumping - Guilty plea.   
Count 3 - Possess Narcotic Drugs (Hydrocodone) - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, burglary.   Motion granted.   Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for thirty (30) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Continue with current treatment program;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) No employment/volunteer work with individuals at risk over age 62;
5) Work/school combination at agent's discretion;
6) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge; 
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined.  
Defendant is given credit for 7 days time already served.   
Cash bail to be applied.   
